    "go:2298": {
      "title": "GATE CSE 1993 | Question: 7.10",
      "year": "gate1993",
      "link": "https://gateoverflow.in/2298/gate-cse-1993-question-7-10",
      "question": "<p>Assume that  the following jobs are to be executed on a single processor system$$\\begin{array}{|c|c|} \\hline  \\textbf{Job Id} &amp; \\textbf{CPU Burst Time} \\\\\\hline \\text{p} &amp; 4 \\\\\\hline  \\text{q} &amp; 1 \\\\\\hline \\text{r} &amp; 8 \\\\\\hline \\text{s} &amp; 1 \\\\\\hline \\text{t} &amp; 2 \\\\\\hline \\end{array}$$The jobs are assumed to have arrived at time $0^+$ and in the order $p,q,r,s,t$. Calculate the departure time (completion time) for job $p$ if scheduling is round robin with time slice $1$</p>\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-alpha\">\n<li>$4$</li>\n<li>$10$</li>\n<li>$11$</li>\n<li>$12$</li>\n<li>None of the above</li>\n</ol>",
      "tags": [
        "gate1993",
        "operating-system",
        "process-scheduling",
        "normal"
      ],
      "question_uid": "go:2298",
      "exam_uid": "cse:1993:set1:main:q7-10",
      "answer_uid": "v2:7.19.4",
      "answer_meta": {
        "type": "MCQ",
        "answer": "C",
        "tolerance": null,
        "source": "question_uid"
      }
    },
    "go:2299": {
      "title": "GATE CSE 1993 | Question: 8.1",
      "year": "gate1993",
      "link": "https://gateoverflow.in/2299/gate-cse-1993-question-8-1",
      "question": "<p>Consider a simple connected graph $G$ with $n$ vertices and $n$ edges $(n &gt; 2)$. Then, which of the following statements are true?</p>\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-alpha\">\n<li>$G$ has no cycles</li>\n<li>The graph obtained by removing any edge from $G$ is not connected</li>\n<li>$G$ has at least one cycle</li>\n<li>The graph obtained by removing any two edges from $G$ is not connected</li>\n<li>None of the above </li>\n</ol>",
      "tags": [
        "gate1993",
        "graph-theory",
        "graph-connectivity",
        "easy",
        "multiple-selects"
