    "go:2312": {
      "title": "GATE CSE 1993 | Question: 15",
      "year": "gate1993",
      "link": "https://gateoverflow.in/2312/gate-cse-1993-question-15",
      "question": "<p>Consider the recursive algorithm given below:</p>\n<pre class=\"prettyprint lang-c_cpp\">procedure bubblesort (n);\nvar i,j: index; temp : item;\nbegin\n    for i:=1 to n-1 do\n        if A[i] &gt; A[i+1] then\n        begin\n            temp := A[i];\n            A[i] := A[i+1];\n            A[i+1] := temp;\n        end;\n    bubblesort (n-1)\nend\n</pre>\n<p>Let $a_n$ be the number of times the ‘if…then…’ statement gets executed when the algorithm is run with value $n$. Set up the recurrence relation by defining $a_n$ in terms of $a_{n-1}$. Solve for $a_n$.</p>",
      "tags": [
        "gate1993",
        "algorithms",
        "recurrence-relation",
        "normal",
        "descriptive"
      ],
      "question_uid": "go:2312",
      "exam_uid": "cse:1993:set1:main:q15",
      "answer_uid": "v2:1.27.8",
      "answer_meta": {
        "type": "MCQ",
        "answer": "B",
        "tolerance": null,
        "source": "question_uid"
      }
    },
